The paper discusses a model for colour categorisation based on the visual cortex, which suggests a focus on computer vision (cs.CV) and neural networks (cs.NE). The use of ellipsoids to represent colour categories and the computation of pixel belongingness also suggest a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper's application to image processing and segmentation suggests a focus on natural language processing (cs.CL).
